stries; and by-products comprising anhydrous ammonia, cyclohexanone, soda ash, gypsum, sulphuric acid, and carbon dioxide. In addition, the company imports fertilizers, including muriate of potash and others; and offers various services for farmers. Further, it engages in engineering consultancy and design; and fabrication and erection of industrial equipment activities. Further, it offers services for farmer, including fact agro service centre, fact marketing network, Prime minister Krishi Samridhi Kendra, soil testing and soil health card, field demonstrations, mobile based fertiliser management system, and drone technology. The Fertilisers and Chemicals Travancore Limited was incorporated in 1943 and is headquartered in Kochi, India."}}